\section*{VENTRICULAR FIBRILLATION AND PULSELESS VENTRICULAR TACHYCARDIA}

Ventricular fibrillation (VF) and pulseless ventricular tachycardia (VT) are life-threatening cardiac rhythms that result in ineffective ventricular contractions. VF is a rapid quivering of the ventricles instead of a forceful contraction. The ventricular motion ofVF is not synchronized with atrial contractions. Pulseless VT occurs when the rapidly contracting ventricles

